stlib.datatypes.time

Class TimeInstant

  • java.lang.Object
    • stlib.datatypes.GeneralType
      • stlib.datatypes.time.TimeInstant
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimeInstantIF>, Orderable<TimeInstantIF>, GeneralTypeIF, TimeInstantIF

    public class TimeInstant
extends GeneralType
implements TimeInstantIF
    Class for representation of the 'Instant' data type.
    Internally the 'java.time.Instant' class is used to store the date time value.

    Stores date time values down to one nanosecond.
    Objects of this class are immutable.

    Author:
    Markus Fuessel
